SINGER Kelly Khumalo is on top of the world. This as the live version of her track Ngathwala Ngaye, featuring Durban vocalist Mondli Ngcobo, reached up to 1,1 million views on YouTube. She took to Instagram, where she posted: “Ngathwala Ngaye featuring @mondlingc is not only on platinum but also has a video on 4 million on YouTube, and now the live version is on 1 million views. They say numbers don’t lie but I say when God shows up, He shows off. Thank you bomakhi bazokhuluma.” ALSO READ : Tbo Touch versus Musa Khawula! Kelly released the song in 2020, that is featured on her album The Volume of Africa. And its original video has 4,4 million views. Ngathwala Ngaye has been trending recently after Advocate Malesela Teffo revealed in court that he would call an eyewitness who would testify that Kelly shot late Bafana Bafana captain Senzo Meyiwa in 2014. He is representing four of the five accused in the murder trial that is proceeding in the North Gauteng High Court.